SIMPLE: nymphalid
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nymphalid
<hw>nymphalid</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>Any butterfly of the family
<fam>Nymphalidae</fam>, consisting of medium to large butterflies found
worldwide, typically having brightly colored wings and much-reduced
nonfunctional forelegs carried folded on the breast.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> nymphalid butterfly, brush-footed butterfly,
four-footed butterfly.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nymphalidae</ent>⟦br⟧
